customers_say: Customers find the bar table easy to assemble and appreciate its quality, noting it's perfect for kitchen nooks and well-built. The table is sturdy, looks nice, and features adjustable height, with one customer mentioning the crank mechanism works well for raising and lowering. While some customers say it's perfect for small spaces, others find it smaller than expected. Several customers report receiving tables with scratched or dented tops after assembly.

top_reviews.review_comment: Awesome table. I was on the fence between the metal top or wood. Went with the gun metal and metal top since there is always a risk of wood color and grain never being what is described. Very pleased. The size is perfect and height adjustment provides more of a range than was described with the total mac height being close to bar top so that was a pleasant surprise. Super easy build. The adjustable screw-drive needs to have a little pressure to engage. I believe that is from the metal top being lighter than the wood. But its still functions fine and smoothly. Great purchase!!
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: I bought this table for my husband‘s 50th birthday. I bought a bourbon barrel top from his favorite bourbon, and swapped out the table top (a friend cut out the center of the table top that came with this table to create a “frame” & them charred it to match the barrel lid). It was the talk of his party! The table is very sturdy and high-quality. It did however come without the final piece on the handle. I contacted Customer Service to ask about the missing piece and got a very friendly and human response the same day. They gave me a tracking number and shipped me a WHOLE NEW TABLE! Such excellent Customer Service with a very unexpected outcome. My friend who helped finish the table is being gifted the replacement one (sans handle, but it’s still fully functional) to make his own bourbon table! Paying it forward. :)
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2024

top_reviews.review_title: Trouble with force-threaded bolts in the foot assembly.
top_reviews.review_comment: I found that one of the bolts in the leg assembly (which needed to be removed in order to attach the ring for the foot rest), had been forced into its hole - against the threads. In order to back it out, I had to use the provided hex key and a long wrench, to back-thread the bolt out. Then when I was assembling the two pieces I had to again use the combination to correctly rethread the bolt into place. One other bolt needed the wrench to re-thread it into place as well. Must have been screwed in with a power tool, which pretty much stripped the threads. The others were fine. Took much too long and much too much effort to assemble that part! Everything else went together easily, with no added effort. I appreciated the included adhesive felt pads for the bottoms of the feet - to protect the floor! Those are not on the parts list, but were a welcome add-on! Very intuitive assembly - no guesswork. Frame and table are very solid and sturdy. The crank mechanism works just fine, as does the lock-arm. The wood table itself has a couple of very small gouges in it, but †he walnut top has a black walnut finish, so they do not show. I applied some furniture polish to disguise the little dings. The overall finish is slightly rough to the touch. I will buy some 0000 steel wool to help smooth it out; then re-polish it again.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2023

top_reviews.review_title: Design flaw: Gear tube too short for screw
top_reviews.review_comment: The media could not be loaded. Nice quality overall but the center screw and tube that ties in the gear handle is designed too short and the handle falls off. The tube needs to be a few millimeters shorter to allow the screw to fully screw in and hold the handle. I've emailed the manufacture for a work around. I like the table enough to not return it, just need this issue resolved. I will leave the review a 1 star until the issue is resolved.
top_reviews.review_date: Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2025

top_reviews.review_comment: The item is well built and sturdy , I am 6’4 and everything feels solid no concerns using this item and it also looks nice .The assembly was simple directions are really not necessary and the included tool works as intended. The iron base is quite heavy not cheap metal . The wood tops are also quite good , surface is a bit rough but that is the intended look . The crank on the table used to adjust the height could be a constructed a bit better but it works fine . The chair and table legs could use protective caps to avoid scratches to floors. This is a great option as an inexpensive seating choice for a small coffee or breakfast area or accent piece . Recommended
